msgctxt "320_Gunrhein"
msgid ""
"\r\n"
"Gunrhein is a shooting game in which you pilot an invincible fighter craft "
"to defend your base units from waves of enemies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "332_Gunrhein"
msgid ""
"\r\n"
"While your fighter is invincible, your base units are destroyed upon "
"contact with an enemy. If you lose all of your base units, you lose."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "344_Gunrhein"
msgid ""
"\r\n"
"Your fighter can't attack enemies. Instead, it places cannons. These "
"cannons fire beam weapons automatically to shoot down enemies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "356_Gunrhein"
msgid ""
"\r\n"
"Once set, a cannon fires until it runs out of energy. It can't rotateÔºçit is "
"set in place based on the fighter's position and direction at the time of "
"placement. Determine the best strategy to effectively shoot down enemy "
"units!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "368_Gunrhein"
msgid ""
"\r\n"
"A cannon's energy only drains if its beam is not hitting enemies. If a "
"cannon loses all of its energy, it will flash red, then disappear."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "380_Gunrhein"
msgid ""
"\r\n"
"When the beams of two or more cannons cross, they combine into a more "
"powerful beam. You can intensify beam weapons by holding down the button "
"before placing a cannon."
msgstr ""

